# Frontend Architecture & UI Design Plan

We will build the Vellum UI adhering to the strict component architecture and the "Midnight Executive" theme you requested, utilizing Tailwind CSS for rapid styling and responsiveness.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please review the file structure and Tailwind theme configuration. Once approved, I will proceed to generate and inject the components into your application.

## 1. Setup Phase: Tailwind CSS Integration

Since Tailwind was excluded in the initial scaffolding, the first step will be to install and configure it for the App Router.

- **Dependencies**: Install `tailwindcss`, `postcss`, `autoprefixer`.
- **Config**: Initialize `tailwind.config.ts` with custom colors for the "Midnight Executive" theme.
- **Global Styles**: Update `src/app/globals.css` with the Tailwind directives.

## 2. File Structure Map

We will enforce a strict separation of concerns within `src/components/`.

```text
src/
└── components/
    ├── layout/
    │   ├── DashboardLayout.tsx   (Responsive wrapper)
    │   ├── Sidebar.tsx           (Desktop fixed left nav)
    │   └── MobileNav.tsx         (Mobile/Tablet bottom bar)
    ├── dashboard/
    │   └── DashboardHome.tsx     (Assembles the main dashboard view)
    └── ui/
        ├── AnalyticsCard.tsx     (Glass-morphism stat block)
        └── ActivityFeed.tsx      (Live AI interaction feed placeholder)
```

## 3. Theme Specification: "Midnight Executive"

We will define these custom values in `tailwind.config.ts`:

- **Obsidian Background**: `bg-obsidian` (`#0F0F13`)
- **Electric Violet Accents**: `text-violet-accent` (`#7B2CBF`)
- **Glass-morphism**: Built using utility combinations like `bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-lg border border-white/10`.

